explanation: The solution works by counting the frequency of each character in both strings, then summing up the absolute differences in counts for each character. Since each difference represents two characters that need to be replaced (one in each string), we divide the total by 2 to get the minimum number of steps. This approach takes advantage of the fact that an anagram has the same character counts, just in a different order.

